item.title: [HIVE-22933] Allow connecting kerberos-enabled Hive to connect to a non-kerberos druid cluster
item.description: Currently, If kerberos is enabled for hive, it can only connect to external druid clusters which are kerberos enabled, Since the Druid client used to connect to druid is always KerberosHTTPClient, This task is to allow a kerberos enabled hiverserver2 to connect to non-kerberized druid cluster.
item.summary: Allow connecting kerberos-enabled Hive to connect to a non-kerberos druid cluster

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.
